    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="68" LastPage="79">
            <pdf>26102-jdecp-rasulov.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>The paper considers a class of nonlinear integro-differential Volterra equations with a logarithmic kernel.
                The study is conducted in a family of weighted spaces on a finite interval with power singularities at its ends.
                Such equations arise in the study of various physical phenomena, including stellar brightness fluctuations, aircraft wing aerodynamics, and processes with memory.
                The article provides a representation of the solution for a nonlinear integro-differential equation with a
                logarithmic kernel and various degrees of nonlinearity.</abstract>
            <title>On the Theory of Integro-differential Nonlinear Volterra Equations with a Logarithmic Kernel</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>logarithmic kernels</word>
                <word>nonlinear equation</word>
                <word>Volterra integro-differential equation</word>
                <word>weight functions</word>
            </keywords>
            <references>
