    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="97" LastPage="120">
            <pdf>26104-jdecp-platonov.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>The paper investigates the stability problem for a class of nonlinear non-stationary complex systems.
                It is assumed that the system is subject to switching and impulsive effects. Different approaches to establishing
                the conditions of the asymptotic stability of a given equilibrium position are proposed.
                These conditions link the constraints on the switching/impulse law and on the rate of change of the non-stationary parameters of the system.
                Note that the described approaches are applicable under broad assumptions about non-stationarities present in the system.
                In particular, the coefficients of the system can be unbounded with respect to time or, conversely, inseparable from zero.
                Finding the required conditions for the asymptotic stability is based on the Lyapunov function method.
                A numerical example is given to illustrate the application of the proved theorems.
                The results obtained can be used in the framework of the problem of the stability analysis of non-stationary systems
                under nonlinear hybrid approximation.</abstract>
            <title>Stability Analysis for Non-stationary Complex Systems with Switching and Impulsive Effects</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>asymptotic stability</word>
                <word>impulsive effects</word>
                <word>non-stationary complex systems</word>
                <word>switching</word>
            </keywords>
            <references>
                <reference>Zubov V. I. Mathematical Methods for the Study of Automatical Control Systems. Oxford, Jerusalem: Pergamon Press, Jerusalem Acad. Press, 1962. 327 p</reference>
                <reference>Liberzon D. Switching in Systems and Control. Boston, MA: Birkhauser, 2003. 233 p</reference>
                <reference>Lakshmikantham V., Bainov D. D., Simeonov P. S. Theory of Impulsive Differential Equations. Singapore: World Scientific, 1989. 288 p</reference>
                <reference>Gao X., Liberzon D., Liu J., Basar T. Unified stability criteria for slowly time-varying and switched linear systems. Automatica. 2018. V. 96. P. 110-120</reference>
                <reference>Wang R., Xing J., Xiang Z., Yang Q. Finite-time stability and asynchronously switching control for a class of time-varying switched nonlinear systems. Transactions of the Institute of Measurement and Control. 2019. V. 42, no. 6. P. 1215-1224</reference>
