    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="121" LastPage="136">
            <pdf>26105-jdecp-shilov.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>We investigate the question of right-boundedness of solutions for a
                model system of ordinary differential equations and their approach to bounded
                solutions. A theorem on the dissipativity of the considered system of equations
                and the existence of bounded solutions is formulated and proved. Conditions
                ensuring the dissipativity of the system are based on a one-sided estimate of the
                coefficient matrix. Under dissipativity conditions, the existence of stationary and
                periodic solutions is proved when the right-hand sides of the system of equations
                are autonomous or periodic. In the case of a constant coefficient matrix, conditions
                equivalent to the one-sided estimate are provided.</abstract>
            <title>Investigation of Boundedness of Solutions to a Model System of Ordinary Differential Equations</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>bounded solution</word>
                <word>dissipative system</word>
                <word>model system of equations</word>
                <word>one-sided estimate</word>
                <word>periodic solution</word>
                <word>stationary solution</word>
            </keywords>
            <references>
