    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="137" LastPage="158">
            <pdf>26106-jdecp-somov.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>Since the 1960s, relay control systems with flywheels and without physical measurement of angular velocity have been successfully used for the satellites orientation due to their simplicity and reliability. Unlike a jet engine, a flywheel creates both active control torque and passive torque through dry friction forces. This is used in a relay amplifier control loop with hysteresis and aperiodic feedback to generate nonlinear oscillations.
                For a third-order differential inclusion with a discontinuous hysteretic  right-hand side, the methods for determining a strong right-hand solution on discontinuity surfaces are analyzed.
                The conditions for solvability of the implicit equation for oscillation periods and the existence of a right-hand solution of this inclusion are presented; the analytical relations for the parameters of the one-sided limit cycle and the conditions for its orbital asymptotic stability are given as well.</abstract>
            <title>Analysis of Nonlinear Oscillations in a Mechatronic Relay Control System with Hysteresis and Digital Tuning</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>differential inclusion</word>
                <word>existence and stability</word>
                <word>hysteresis</word>
                <word>limit cycle</word>
                <word>nonlinear oscillations</word>
                <word>relay system</word>
            </keywords>
