    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="159" LastPage="168">
            <pdf>26107-jdecp-khakimova.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>This article is dedicated to V.F. Zaytsev (September 29, 1945 - February 13, 2018), the founder of discrete-group analysis of ordinary differential equations. The article covers the main stages of Professor V.F. Zaytsev's life, his teaching and research activities, and discusses the diverse hobbies of this talented and multifaceted individual. Among other things, it presents little-known facts about V.F. Zaytsev's biography. At the end of the article, a list of Valentin Fedorovich's major works and the covers of most of his books - monographs and reference works - are included.</abstract>
