    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="169" LastPage="183">
            <pdf>26108-jdecp-lyamin.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>This paper presents an automated approach for the analysis of thyroid ultrasound images, which is based on a combination of the Haar wavelet transform, local density function, and Haralick texture features. The proposed method includes partitioning the annotated ultrasound images into non-overlapping blocks followed by extraction of spatial-frequency, multifractal, and statistical texture characteristics.  For tissue classification Support Vector Machine (SVM) classifier is used. To evaluate the influence of block size and feature extraction parameters on classification performance a comparative study was conducted. The experimental results demonstrate that the best performance is achieved by using 32Г—32 pixel blocks and the Haralick texture features computed with a distance set {1, 2, 3, 4}. To perform automated image labeling the software system implementing the proposed algorithms was developed. The obtained results confirm the effectiveness of the combined mathematical approach for improving the diagnostic accuracy of the thyroid nodule detection.</abstract>
            <title>Analysis of Thyroid Ultrasound Images Using Wavelet Transform and Local Density Function</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>Haar wavelet transform</word>
                <word>Haralick texture features</word>
                <word>image analysis</word>
                <word>local density function</word>
                <word>multifractal analysis</word>
                <word>thyroid gland</word>
                <word>ultrasound imaging</word>
            </keywords>
