    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="184" LastPage="202">
            <pdf>26109-jdecp-kuznetsov-nv.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>This paper studies a modified Chua system with a discontinuous signum nonlinearity. Periodic regimes are localized using the harmonic balance method, Boiko locus, and event-driven numerical simulation by Piiroinen-Kuznetsov method. A hidden stable limit cycle is found for one parameter set, while a self-excited stable limit cycle is obtained for another.</abstract>
            <title>Analysis of the Dynamics of the Chua Circuit with Relay Characteristics</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>Boiko locus</word>
                <word>Chua system</word>
                <word>harmonic balance method</word>
                <word>hidden attractor</word>
                <word>symmetric periodic solution</word>
                <word>the locus of a perturbed relay system</word>
            </keywords>
            <references>
                <reference>T. Matsumoto. A chaotic attractor from Chua’s circuit. IEEE Transactions on Circuits and Systems, 31:1055-1058, 1984</reference>
                <reference>L. O. Chua, M. Komuro, and T. Matsumoto. The double scroll family. IEEE Transactions on Circuits and Systems, CAS-33(11):1072-1118, 1986</reference>
                <reference>N. V. Kuznetsov, T. N. Mokaev, V. I. Ponomarenko, E. P. Seleznev, N. V. Stankevich, and L. Chua. Hidden attractors in Chua circuit: mathematical theory meets physical experiments. Nonlinear Dynamics, 111(6):5859-5887, 2023</reference>
                <reference>N. V. Kuznetsov. Theory of hidden oscillations and stability of control systems. Journal of Computer and Systems Sciences International, 59(5):647-668, 2020</reference>
